LAFIA – As part of the effort to tack­le poverty at the grassroots, the federal government through the Ministry of Humanitarian Affairs, Di­saster Management and So­cial Development has em­powered about 2,600 rural women in Nasarawa State. The Minister, Sadiya Umar Farouq, who made the disbursement in Lafia, said the effort was to im­prove household consump­tion. Sadiya explained the money was to improve school enrollment, at­tendance and encourage household financial capac­ity. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Sadiya, who was repre­sented by the Minister of State for Science and Tech­nology, Barrister Abdulla­hi Mohammed explained that Nasarawa State has received N3.2bn from feder­al government conditional cash transfer programme.